Anena Burger, Netwerk24(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Upington &ndash; A primary school teacher is set to appear in the Upington Magistrate's Court on Monday, charged with sexually assaulting a minor girl.The 28-year-old woman was arrested on Friday, Netwerk24 reported.Police spokesperson Captain Jacques September said she faces charges of rape, molestation, indecent sexual assault and serious assault of a minor.The Northern Cape education department's Geoffrey van der Merwe said in a statement on Sunday that the Laerskool Oranje-noord teacher was immediately suspended."The department and the teaching fraternity are shocked and saddened by the incident," Van der Merwe said."Teachers are secondary caregivers to our children and for that reason we condemn these actions in the strongest terms."He called upon any other pupils who have experienced sexual assault at the hands of a teacher to come forward.Van der Merwe said this kind of behaviour wouldn't be tolerated.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.